Actually I had played on the TriStar that kevtris had, and the sound was perfect.  Maybe the DPCM was louder, I'm not sure because it was quite a while back.  But I do know that every nes-on-a-chip clone I've tried since then has had the screwed pulse duty cycles.  I suppose it's possible they changed to another chip during production.  IIRC, the 'NOAC' was on it's own little carrier board, which would sorta suggest that.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Wed Jun 06, 2012 6:17 pm</p><hr />
